@node ANMERKUNGEN "Remarks"
@prev AUTOR
@next START

   ClickClose requires the standard "@{b}Workbench@{ub}" menu (OS2.1 to OS3.1).

   If it is not available although there is a "Workbench Screen", nothing
   happens, at all.

   If there is a modified "Workbench" menu, possible results range
   from ęnothing happensĽ to ęa trip to indiaĽ ∑X

   If you have a standard workbench and commodities which basically don't
   modify it there are no problems. (For example, in my Workbench environment
   ClickClose runs together with Magic Menu without any problems).

   One strange but harmless bug should be mentioned here:

   Sometimes (very, very rarely) ClickClose refused its work (e.g. after
   leaving MuchMore 3.3 with numericpad 5) until I pressed any key..:(

@endnode
